'Pants man' selfie: Prostate cancer patient Kurt Jewson shares new picture

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A prostate cancer patient whose "pants man" selfie went viral has shared another picture one year on after a "pretty grotty time".

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Kurt Jewson, 45, was hailed a "total hero" for sharing the picture - which showed him in his underwear with a catheter, stoma bag and scars.
Now undergoing radiotherapy, he has shared another picture to encourage men to learn more about the illness.
He said "things could have been different" had he been more aware.
Sharing both pictures on Facebook, Mr Jewson, from west Cornwall, said: "'Pants man' returns, one year on... even more tubby, pale and middle aged than before!"
