Mr Jewson said his "world went into hyper mode" and said he received numerous messages from people affected by cancer.
"These messages were sometimes heart-warming, and sometimes tragic," he said. "To be honest, for a while it all became a bit much for me.
"I was struggling with my own cancer, and at the same time I vowed to myself to reply to every single person who had written to me."
Mr Jewson's radiotherapy will finish in March and his hormone treatment should end in September.
"Fingers crossed... I'm going on to have a long and happy cancer-free life," he said.
